In conclusion I wish to say that the entire State movement is in good order with the exception of Local

Day ton.

This affair has been more or less annoying tthe state office during my entire administration, and

which dates back a number of years during the administration of former secretaries. It is to be hoped that this

convention will clear up this matter by thoroughly investigating all charges and reports concerning the at-

fairs.

As the matter now stands the State Secretary is thoroughly convinced that Local Dayton should be

made to understand that the State organization is larger than any local and should always be respected as
such. However, this is a matter to be settled by the convention and 1 will not linger longer on this question.
Another question which I wish to mention is the fact that 1 am not a candidate for re-election to the office
of State Secretary. Thanking you for your kind attention, I am.

