Constitution. \

It is the opinion of the State Secretary that the State Constitution should be so revised as to make it a
stable program to work by. The present wording of the law of the constiution is so that it can be inter-
preted in various ways, which is not only confusing to those who choose to do right, but it also gives “lee-
way” to those who have ulterior motives, and inasmuch as We have ample time in the four days that we will
be assembled here, we can redraft this document and make it at least substantial enough to afford a medium
to guide our party in the future, or at least up to such time when it becomes necessary to again revise it.
I suggest that special care should be taken in doing this. _ 0

